-- Deutsche Bahn Narrows Arriva Germany Bids to Four, Sueddeutsche Reports
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2010-10-30T10:39:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-30/deutsche-bahn-narrows-arriva-germany-bids-to-four-sueddeutsche-reports.html
Deutsche Bahn AG  aims to conclude
the sale of its Arriva unit’s German arm in November and has
four shortlisted bidders,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported, citing
unidentified people on the railway operator’s supervisory board.  The potential buyers are France’s Veolia Environnement SA,
Keolis, the infrastructure fund Cube as well as Abellio GmbH, a
subsidiary of Netherlands Railways, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Cornelius Rahn  in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  